</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How could God let this happen?</span><hr size=1> Although the Bible does include many of the convenience laws we hold today.(it's inconvenient for people to murder each other, steal, etc.)  The law is probably a much better teacher over all.  It tells you what you're allowed, and what you're not allowed to do in our &quot;civilized&quot; society.  The Bible mixes in stoning gays, and the vengeance of the all mighty God into the equasion, and thus may not be the best life teacher.  Of course most people from the big 3(and other religions) edit down their religious books for content.  Not that there's anything wrong with that I suppose.  Just trying to say that we take from our religious texts what we put into it.<br>
<br>
As for Charles Darwin's theories, it's silly to state that since he didn't believe we share a common link with primates, that we don't.  It was a rough theory, a first draft, that has gone through a lot of &quot;edits&quot; over the years.  Darwin never claimed that everything he said was necessarily correct, he merely proposed a theory based on his observations.  We have expanded on what he originally came up with, to something we consider more correct.<br>
<br>
As for many important historical figures rolling in their grave?  Who would these be?  Your heroes from 1500 years ago may not approve of the lifestyle of your heroes for 500 years ago.  Judging our society by the beliefs of someone who lived in an age when they could not possibly experience what we do now, is kinda silly.<br>
<br>
What happened to turn the other cheek anyways?<br>
<br>
